        'feed' => 'Chenar Faryab (Persian: چنارفارياب, also Romanized as Chenār Fāryāb, Chenār-e Fāryāb, and Chenār Fārīāb; also known as Chenār Pāryāb) is a village in Kuh Mareh Sorkhi Rural District, Arzhan District, Shiraz County, Fars province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 332, in 74 families.\n\n\n== References ==',
