        'title' => 'Bakırlı, Pertek',
        'feed' => 'Bakırlı (Kurdish: Şûşang) is a village in the Pertek District, Tunceli Province, Turkey. The village is populated by Kurds of the Pilvenk tribe and had a population of 41 in 2021.\nThe hamlets of Aşağınaçar and Yukarınaçar are attached to the village.\n\n\n== References ==',
