        'title' => 'Thryssa kammalensis',
        'feed' => 'Thryssa kammalensis, the Kammal thryssa, is a species of ray-finned fish in the family Engraulidae. It is found in the western Indo Pacific.\n\n\n== Size ==\nThis species reaches a length of 18.0 cm (7.1 in).\n\n\n== Etymology ==\nThe fish is named in honor of a place: Kammal in Java, Indonesia, the locality where the type specimen was found.\n\n\n== References ==',
